Pointer 44.4 (16.7.99)

 Added images

 Save/Use/Test should work

 New colorwheel.gadget is disabled for pen 0

 Opens new screen if not at least 4 colors can be obtained exclusiv.

Pointer 44.5 (30.7.99)

 Hot spot coordinates were negative.

 Loading hot spot didn't work at all.

 slider no longer flickers while dragging Colorwheel or gradient

Pointer 44.6 (31.7.99)

 added stack extension

 Reset to Defaults, Restore and Cancel didn't set the pointer resolution.

Pointer 44.7 (10.8.99)

 again changed the handling of the pointer resolution. Bug reports are not
  reproducable.

 added range checking for hot spot

 default busy pointer had hot spot at wrong place

Pointer 44.8 (11.8.99)

 pointer is now limited to the visible size (16x24 for Lo-Res, 32*48 for 
  Hi-Res) while saving

 "Restore Colors" and pasting images did not update the palette on high/true
  color screens.

 the 4 sample pointer also restricted to the visible size.

 gradientslider is limited to only 6 exclusive pens and one shared pen now.
  This is still enough to look quite good.

Pointer 44.9 (12.8.99)

 pasting/loading images trashed palette on non 8-8-8 screens.

 colors were loaded after refreshing sketchboard which is wrong under
  hi/true color screens

Pointer 44.11 (16.8.99)

퇏disabled some debuging code (screen was opened behind)

Pointer 44.12 (17.8.99)

 removed blue box behind tool buttons

 added close gadget

 added seperator line

 modified Save/Use/Cancel layout

 user can now resize height too.

 RGB/HSV color model items were not marked as mutual exclude

 After setting the hot spot the tool that was selected before is set again

 changed refresh of palette on Hi/True color screen (less flickering). 
  Palette is now updated while moving colowheel, gradient or color sliders

 Handling of "Reset Colors" was broken

 Renamed "Reset Colors" to "Restore Colors" because this is more what it
  does

Pointer 44.13 (8.9.99)

 Doubleclicking a prefs project now loads this project and performs the 
  ACTION. This didn't work for WB Startup before.

 Loading an image did use wrong file requester title and missed the image
  filter hook

Pointer 44.14 (16.9.99)

 new project icon name def_pointer_prefs

 changed tool images

 fixed a bug that made loading or pasting images nearly useless.

 RGB sliders now use values from 0 to 255 instead of real hardware dependend
  color range.

Pointer 44.16 (28.9.99)

 fixed a bug in framework: "Open" a prefs file did not show any files in
  the file requester if a image or sound file was loaded before because the
  file filter function was not reset.

